review_blob:
Draft from my house: keg is multiple months old poured into a dimple mug
pours extremely black and opaque with a large creamy espresso tan head that last for ever.  very rich malt aroma with a big licorice and dark chocolate aromas, small hints of some roast coffee but not over powering. very inviting nose. big thick chewy mouth feel and a nice warming and smooth drinking beer. great chocolate flavors with hints of roast and coffee and nice bright licorice moments. extremely smooth and creamy for an impy stout. excellent drinker and has aged well
beer_name: Terrapin Side Project Big Daddy Vladys Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Draft at coasters: pours a nice dark brown with some hazelnut high lights, small tan head. Flavor us a fantastic mellow coffee with a nice hint of chocolate and a sutle roast. Fantastic flavor of coffee one of the best i have had. Aroma is a soft chocolate and a gentle toast and nice coffee. A very well done beer.
beer_name: Cigar City Cubano-Style Espresso Brown Ale

review_blob: Bottle from SS: pours beautiful clear amber gold with a large off white standing head and great lacing. Aroma is full of hops that are both citrus and pine, some good sweet malts behind the hops. Very nice. Flavor is a ton of hop bitterness that clings to the tongue. Good piney hop flavor and the malt swewtness creeps in at the end.

Bottle: pours with a large off white head that stays. This sits atop a hazy amber brown body. Aroma is full of sweet spices; cardomon mostly but good orange and corriander very nice. Nice estery dark ftuits blend great with the spices, awsome aroma one of the best spice beer aromas i have had. Wow the flavor is great the mix of spices and dark fruits is fantastic. Some alcohol sneaks in yo let you know that you arw drinking a big beer.

Bottle: pours a dark dark brown with no head. Aroma is chocolatey woth some earthy spice and toffee malts very enjoyable. Flavor is a soft chocolate and a rich spicey roast. A thin mouthfeel at first then a heavy spice finish.

Bottle: pours a clear amber color with a small off white head. Aroma is full of spice plenty of cinnamon, clove, nutmeg, a little bit of the pumpkin comes through also. Flavor is also has plenty of the spice and lots of pumpkin, no hops but very drinkable and a nice pumpkin beer.

Bottle with homer321: pours a dark cola brown with a large tan head. Aroma is a rich malt with some dark chocolate notes, little to no hops. Flavor is very rich malt again and pkenty of chocolate, little of the maple syrup. A good brown ale but not spectacular.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada / Dogfish Head Life & Limb

review_blob: Can from tyler: pours beautiful golden color crystal clear with a large white head that lasts. Aroma is very nice full of sweetness from the pilsen malt, very clean great hop aroma for style, get some honey like aroma also. Slight crisp fruit but not yeast dirived, maybe hops. Flabor is full and clean with a slight sweetness, good hop flavor bit could use more bittering. Very easy to drink and would love a case. Needs to be a lottle dryer in finish.
beer_name: Daves BrewFarm Select Golden Lager - Canned

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bottle cheese: pours very black and dead flat. Aroma is all bourbon a little wood and some roast, dark chocolate sneaks in also. Flavor is very chocolate and again borboun dominate. Some wood also and plenty of alcohol. This beer hurts.
beer_name: Port Brewing Santas Little Helper - Bourbon Barrel

review_blob: Bottle solan: pours cloudy orangey yellow no head small white line around glass. Aroma is sour amd Funky, fresh very tart apple, flower blossoms, honey, peppery, earthy, just fantastic and complex. Flavor is very sour but with plenty of flavor again with pepper, honey, tart tart apple and hints of earthy flowers. The most sour Cantillion yet. Awesome

Bottle moejuck: pours pretty still no head beautiful cherry brown color. Aroma rocks woody, cherry, malty, slight tart. Holy shit this flavor is fantastic full of cherry and the wood flavor is great. Tartness is near perfect.

Growler solan: pours good dark ice tea brown with a small off white head. Aroma is good and earthy nice fresh hops some maple and a good malty presence. Flavor is good a liitle hops and some of the maple comes through too. Not a ton of flavors but what is there is pleasant. Nice rich malt came out as it warms.

Bottle cheese: pours good and clear medium off white head. Aroma is very herbal and earthy, sweet, slight fruittiness also. Very odd combination. Flavor is thin with a little earthy flavor with some anise and a slight roast. Odd combination might not be the best idea.

Bottle cheese: pours beautifully very dark brown with a good lasting tan head lots of bubbles. Aroma is great full of clean roast, nice bread, and good toffee malts. Flavor is good very lots of carbonation, good roast, vhocolate and good drying finish. Very drinkable

Bottle cheese: pours awesome color of red wine, nice legs. Very sweet aroma with a little of the blueberry and slight vinous. Good honey also. Flavor is plenty of honey and very little of the fruit, they honey flavor rules this one great mead.

Bottle from cheese: pours a light murky lemonaid yellow very thin white line head. Good light aroma with a little straw small fruit and a touch of the funk, light popcorn. Good light mouthfeel and light taste some fruit very nice and very drinkable.

Bottle atleast 1 year old: pours a very bubbly ice tea brown with a medium soapy tan head with some lacing. Aroma is grainy with plenty of caramel malt and a little toffee. Also some sweet sugars and an aroma of agimg hops, some underlying fruit character too. Flavor is a little weak at first then warms quickly. Lots of grainy bitterness and flavor, slight caramel and just to much grain bitterness, some older hop flavor too. Not a great BW but drinkable.
beer_name: Santa Fe Chicken Killer Barley Wine

review_blob: Pours very lively with a big. Off white cloudy head, some soapy lacing above a cola brown body. Aroma at first is a fresh gingerbread cookie that is bready, cinnamon, ginger, and a little nutmeg. The bready cookie aroma is awesome. The flavor is much the same with plenty of the spice and a great bready brown malt taste. A very spicey good thanksgiving beer. Not sure i could drink more than one at a sitting though.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Frosted Frog Christmas Ale

review_blob:
Bottle 12oz: pours a murky chestnutty brown with a large off white head that stays as a thin line. Aroma is full of beautiful malts, caramellt, rich toffee, and a decent hop aroma that is very earthy. Also some brown sugae notes that compliment well. Some fantastic baked cherries come out as it warms. Fantastic
flavor is very malty but a good balancing hop bitterness. The flavor is extremly mellow and a real joy to drink   Dlight waing reminds you of the alcohol a great barley wine.

Bottle: pours a beautiful dark ice tea brown with a small tan head that goes quickly. Aroma is interesting with some sourness slight roast and a little smokiness, under that is a very nice chocolate. This smells just like my old english porter. Flavor is quick tart sourness that dominates at first, then a very little roast comes and a touch of the chocolate. Finishs tart and dry. Even with the odd sourness i really enjoy this beer as I drink it. 
Im back already to add to my rating. This beer warms up and turns to someting amazing. I get the slight oak now and an awesom caramel maltness both aroma and taste  i also get some fruity esters that are so inviting. All and all this beer is awesome and grew on me for sure.
beer_name: New Glarus Unplugged Old English Porter

review_blob: bottle: pours very very dark brown near black but some highlights show up when help to the light. thick off white head that just sits flat and stays. very nice aroma good estery and phenolic yeast. that is slight spice and a little banana, some sweeter malts blend in and a very very small chocolate note.  Flavor is a bit odd for style nothing is really blending well together for some reason. Plenty of spiciness that is oddly paired with chocolatey malts. not much of the banana comes through that was in the nose.  not a bad beer, and can be drank but the flavors do not seem to go together in this and dont play well with each other. would like to see what this does with even more time, but not sure if it will meld.

Can; pours a very dark brown with a large creamy tan head that has soapy lacing, good head retention. Aroma is very coffee with a hints of coffee grounds, some nuttiness amd a little chocolate notes. Also seems like some oats are present. Flavor is heavy coffee at first bit melds into nice chocolate, nuttiness, and good creaminess in the mouth feel. Very nice beer but not nearly as good as regular Bender.

Bottle: pours a nice gold colir large white head with a little lacing. The aroma is awesome full of a fresh sweet pine aroma with a nice malt behind. Flavor is great too, plenty of fresh hops that have a good sweet pinyness and a hint of citrus plenty of malt to hold this together.

Bottle 33cl   Pours near dead dark cola brown no head. Aroma is fantastic tons of vanilla hits me at first then a nice crabapple tart fruit. Slight honey and a near vinegar sour. Very good just got some great dried dark fruit. Flavor is a very light sourness of unripe granny smith apples and crabapples, dry fruit of figs, and just a little sweetness believe it or not great beer could be a little more sour.

Bottle: pours a cloudy medium hay gold color large white head with
a soapy lacing, good head retention. Aroma is very herbal and spicey 
nice peepry that i love, earthy gingery aroma, nice flower and a touch of 
honey. Flavor is quite a bit of spice. Peppery and herbal good sweetness like honey. Very dry in the finish with just a little warming.

bottle from Growler: pours black as can be with a large coffee colored head. A very odd aroma form the first time i had it. Starts with a sour note then fades right into the dark chocolates, cherry, and some roasted coffee but very little. alot like dark chocolate covered cherry aroma.
flavor is full of chocolate a mix of dark and milky smooth chocolate though, a slight almost burnt roast that gives a little drying in the finish the flavor has a little of the cherry like fruit and a slight tartness, but extremely smooth impy stout. very nice stout with a great little hint of sourness that fits well and gives a different flavor to a stout.

Can brought back from Spain: pours incredibly clear and very light golden straw small white head lingers awhile. Aroma is sweet slight grassy hops and a little fruiiness pretty crisp. Flavor is very clean some pretty good hop bitterness and a little hop flavor smooth with noajor flaws seems to be right on for style. Dont know if this seems so good because it is canned and fresh from spain but way better than average score says.

Bottle from paulp: pours crystal vlear with a large mousey white head and beautiful lacing. Aroma is full of hops lots of pine and grassiness and a little bit of citrus some good malt sweetness sneeks in. Flavor is very nice a good honey like sweetness goes great with the piney grassy hops again with just a hint of citrus that also seems to add a little sweetness. Very good ipa glad to try it and have another one.
beer_name: Captain Lawrence Captains Reserve Imperial IPA

review_blob: Bottle cant believe i have not rated this one:  pours a beautiful ruby brown color with a small tan head. Aroma has a great spice sweet nutty malt very good cinnamon notes. A very slight roasty also. Flavor is a good spice next mix with cinnamon and other christmas spices nutty malts and a slight sweetness. Good holiday drinker

Bottle: pours a dark chestnut brown with a good sized tan head. Aroma is a sweet nuttiness, toffee malts, and a little diacytle, but ok not over powering. Very low amount of hops also. Flavor is again nutty with some dry roast character and a touch of chocolate again low hop flavor. I really enjoy this porter to bad i have to buy it in the 12 pack to get just 2.
UPDATED: NOV 20, 2009

Bottle with atleast a year on it:  wow cant beloeve i jave mot rated this one. Pours a very clear dark straw golden color with a good white head that last. Aroma is awesome full of peepery goodness, herbal chamomile, slight brett, sweet malts, apricot mango like fruit. Just full of so much. I love it. Flavor  is also peppery with a slight tart and a good sugary sweetness. Nice tingly palate a world class saison.

Bottle from Growler:  pours with a large soapy white head atop a vlear golden body.  Aroma is fantastic crisp pils malt sweet hops and a real joy to smell a slight fruity aroma that is very good. Flavor is very goid great pils malt flavor and sweetness with a good hop bitterness and excellent hop flavor. All the flavors blend well and make this a fsntastic beer to drink

Bottle: pours. Clearish chestnut brown with a large off white head that last with great lacing. Aroma has a good caramel malt and a some toasty old bread aroma. Also some english hops that seem to be fading. Very small amount of fruity esters. Flavor is a bready dry toast flavor some decent caramel   Hop bitterness plays well with the beer.

Bottle 46/204: pours a dark brown some amber hues come through also small tan head with some lacing. Aroma is great full of all different smells rich malts some very good barrell and great hints of vanilla very slight roast great balance of aromas  flavor is very full and lively great rich malts and a good hint of alcohol some of the wood comes through. Very enjoyable and great.

Bottle. Pours a beautiful cloudy straw gold with tons of tiny carbonation bubbles. A quick medium white head. Aroma is great slight funk tartness not  over powering a nice tropical fruit good sweet malt and a tinge of bright citrus and a good honey note.  i love it.  Flavor is a bit weaker than expected but very nice slight lemon and a tiny tart funk extremly easy to drink and unbelievably refreshing. I love this beer wish more was available would make a great session beer

Bomber. Pours an slightly cloudy amber color with a soapy bubble off white head. Aroma is a subtle hop aroma that is slightly soapy and not pungent at all. Also dome pretty goid malt with a nice toffe crystal malt aroma. Flavour is a grassy hop bitterness with a nice malt background some grainy bitterness  also the malt is present but pretty much covered up by the bitterness all the hops seem to be fir bittering and not flavor. I really dont know why you would dry hop with magnum no flavor

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Bottle atleast 1 year old. Pours a cloudy Monet golden wheat color large fluffy white head. Aroma is a slight musty lemon smell, some good malt grain and a slight sugar also, slight aging hop presence. Odd but very enjoyable. Flavor is quite grainy and musty a decent hop bitterness gives a good mouthfeel   Not a ton of flavor but very easy drinking and enjoyable could easily drink more

Bottle. Pours a dark chocolate brown with a small tan head that lingers. Aroma is very roasty some chocolate and very little to no rye. Some decent toffee like sweetness also no hops. Flavor is very smooth with a silky chocolate and a good roast chatacter that plays well with the drying rye. Overall a very drinkable beer

Bomber bottle. Pours very clear burnt orange color with a very large off white head that stays for ever. Aroma is a bit soapy, could be casacade hops, also get some earthy slight pine hops and some malt hides in background. Flavor is  a bit weak with a thin mouthf fell and a slight hop bitterness and flavor   Flavor is an odd dish towel like also. Drinkable but not overly enjoyable

Bottle. Pours a murky brown amber color with a medium tan head good lacing. Aroma is very grainy some american hop slips through it, sweet caramel malts linger also. A bit dirty aroma but not bad. Flavor is also dirty tasting with plenty of graininess, some bitter hops and very low flavor hops not great but i will finish the bottle.

Bottle from uncle. Pours very clear amber with a large lacy fluffy white head. Aroma is citrusy with plenty of cascade hops nice malt background with a good crystal malt aroma very nice. Flavor is on the bitter hop side with some malt background   Very smooth and easy drinking flavor just does not live up to look and aroma. Great session beer though

Bottle from my uncle. Pours a beautiful lacy mousy white heas that sits on a clear dark straw body. Aroma is fantastic plenty of amarillo hops and some citrus notes. The rye comes through very well  slight graininess also. Flavor is a bit flat some hops come through atop a weak sweetened malt rye character is present but low. A beautiful beer with a great aroma just a lscking flavour.

Bottle. Pours a very nice dark cola brown big froathy tan head. Aroma is malty, brown malt aroma, earthy spice some fruity esters ok but not great for the style. Flavor is malty and earthy a slight roastiness that i enjoy slight esters ok again. Overall very drinkable and I enjoy it.

Pours a very clear orange amber with a small white head. The aroma is swewt with plenty of honey and a nice caramelly malt. The hops dont quite balance the sweetness but are very effident somw fruity esters are there giving it an almost english ale character    The flavor is veey nice and smooth with a good hop bitterness and flavor. The malt seems to play the background but plays it well the honey flavor seems to be lost in the flavor the fruity esters are there also. Overall this is a nice drinking beer that seems to resemble an English ale to me.

bottle from joekinty: pours a very pretty reddish cooper with little to no head. aroma is good sweet and malty, some suagars also, slight spice. flavour is sweet and the spice comes through nicely. the malt is there and pretty caramelly. a very nice drinking beer with very little of the alcohol coming through. good beer.
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Outta Kilter Wee Heavy Scotch Red Ale

review_blob:
bottle shared by ibrew2or3: 
pours  chocolate brown with a small tan head.  aroma is very sweet, slightly smokey, good fruitness too, touch of roast.  flavour is light not much smoke and gets sweet. finish is a little dry not to bad.

bottle shared by thecheeseman:
pours beautiful dusky red grape juice colour with little to no head. aroma is great full of grapes slight sour and funk a great fruit to it also. flavour is so smooth with a little sour and just a fantastic fruit. finish is just as smooth as can be.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob:
bottle shared by thecheeseman:
pours a cloudy bright orange almost no head just a thin white head line. aroma is awesome great tartness, good sour and a nice sweetness that follows. some fruit and just a great all round aroma. flavour is just fantastic tart and great funky sour, the finish is smooth as hell with some sweetness perfect finish and palate.

bottle from joekinty: pours  a clear .copper couler with a nice soapy white head, very nice colour.  aroma is awesome full of orangy citrus hops and great malt backbone to balance very nicely a littel of the oak comes through very well not over powering but blends in well. a littel breadiness and a slight cotton candy sweetness. very good. flavour is interesting at frist but then tuns into something very nice. good oak that seems to be sweetened with the malt and a good balance of caramelly malts.  wow i really olike this much better than i thought. great job ST
